node.text:
Going to share this with you ‼️ It’s been a absolute awesome year for our YouTube channel “The Deegans”
 What started just having fun filming some videos on our phones that  turned into absolute cool  way to tell the family story our way. By the numbers it has become one of the most influential  dirtbike channels in existence. Thanks to you guys!! And I feel like we’re only getting started with the stories that are still yet to be told. A ton of work has gone into this many many hours of filming and editing. Special thanks to @gavenayala @ayalamedia and @buckywya our full time film guys that are part of the family always with us! (Putting up with the kids) It is a massive undertaking to put out five videos a week! Remember when we used to do one video a year? It is super satisfying seeing the results of so many people that consistently watch the channel and influences many to get into a healthy lifestyle  and the dirtbike world.  Like I said this has been a strong year for our channel as you can see the millions and millions of views  buy our audience that is absolutely global so many countries tune in !! Never thought there would be a system that would have such a global reach like this !!. Used to be Crusty Demons video once a year ha ha.! We r happy to see the almost billion hours watched  but make sure you take time to get out and ride your dirtbike!! Much love !! Now go out take some big risks and stay crazy!! #TheDeegans #dirtbike #moto #race #family #youtube  Link in bio to sub!  We are always open for cool ideas and colabs also ..

node.text: Had to repost this from @greglaurie Lead pastor at Harvest ( The church I 1st gave my life to Christ ) His words are powerful. I have to pay respects to The families that endured this massive tragic loss. It’s hits hard how young they were. My daughter just turned 20 . I couldn’t imagine .  And many of the soldiers from our area in SoCal.  I’m sorry. They will not be forgotten . We pray for your healing. From our family to yours. 🙏🏼

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by BrianDeegan38 on August 29, 2021 tagging @greglaurie. May be an image of 2 people, people standing, military uniform and outdoors.

Photo shared by BrianDeegan38 on August 29, 2021 tagging @greglaurie. May be an image of 11 people, people standing and text that says 'Rest In Peace Gone but never forgotton LCpl David Espinoza Sgt Nicole Gee SSgt aylor Hoover Cpl Hunter Lopez LCpl Rylee McCollum LCpl Dylan Merola Cpaeem Nikoui Cpl Daegan Page Sgt Johanny Rosario 1R × LCpl Jare Schmitz greglaurie SSG Ryan Knauss Corpsman Max Soviak'.
Photo shared by BrianDeegan38 on August 29, 2021 tagging @greglaurie. May be an image of standing.

Photo shared by BrianDeegan38 on August 29, 2021 tagging @greglaurie. May be an image of text that says 'greglaurie This is Marine Corps Lance Cpl Kareem Nikoui of Norco, California. He is a is one of the 11 Marines who died in the terrorist attack in Afghanistan. Five hours before Kareem made the ultimate sacrifice he was filming a young Afghan girl telling her he was her friend. Kareem was there with other members of our military rescuing people in Afghanistan. I spoke with Kareem's parents, Steve and Shana today. They told me that their whole'.

Photo shared by BrianDeegan38 on August 29, 2021 tagging @greglaurie. May be an image of text that says 'I spoke with Kareem's parents, Steve and Shana today. They told me that their whole family including Kareem had made commitments to Christ at the Harvest Crusade. reminded them of the hope of Scripture that tells us we will see our loved one's again in Heaven, as that is where Kareem is. I am so sorry for the 13 brave Americans who lost their lives. They are all true heroes. Remember to pray for their families today. (Kareem is pictured here with his mother, Shana)'.

Photo shared by BrianDeegan38 on August 29, 2021 tagging @greglaurie. May be an image of text that says 'These are the names of all the serviceman who died for their nation-Ryle McCollum, 20 David L. Espinoza, 20 Kareem Nikoui, 20 Jared Schmitz, 20 Dylan Merola, 20 Hunter Lopez, 22 Humberto Sanchez, 22 Maxton Soviak, 22 Nicole Gee, 23 Daegan Page, 23 Ryan Knauss, 23 Johanny Rosariopichardo, 25 Darin Hoover Jr., 31'.
